# DriveSync — LocalStorage ↔ Google Drive

Back up your browser's localStorage to your own Google Drive. Clean, secure, no third-party servers.

---

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.html` | The web app — host this on GitHub Pages |
| `Code.gs` | Paste this into Google Apps Script |

---

## Setup Guide (one-time, ~5 minutes)

### Step 1 — Create the Apps Script

1. Go to [script.google.com](https://script.google.com) and click **New Project**
2. Delete any existing code, paste the contents of `Code.gs`
3. At the top, **change** `USERNAME` and `PASSWORD` to your own values:
   ```js
   USERNAME : "yourname",
   PASSWORD : "your-secret-password",
   ```
4. Click **Save** (Ctrl+S)

### Step 2 — Deploy as Web App

1. Click **Deploy → New Deployment**
2. Click the gear icon next to "Type" → select **Web app**
3. Set:
   - **Description**: DriveSync
   - **Execute as**: Me
   - **Who has access**: Anyone
4. Click **Deploy**
5. **Copy the Web App URL** (looks like `https://script.google.com/macros/s/ABC.../exec`)

> ⚠️ **Save this URL somewhere safe** — email it to yourself, or use the "Backup URL to Drive" button in the app after first login.

### Step 3 — Host on GitHub Pages

1. Create a GitHub repository
2. Upload `index.html` to it
3. Go to **Settings → Pages → Source → main branch**
4. Your app is live at `https://yourusername.github.io/reponame/`

### Step 4 — First Login

1. Open your GitHub Pages URL
2. Paste your **Web App URL** from Step 2 → Continue
3. Enter your **username and password** → Sign in
4. Click **Settings → Backup URL to Drive** to save your URL to Drive

---

## How it works

- **Export**: Select localStorage keys → choose an App Name → Export to Drive
  - Saved as `DriveSync_Backups/{AppName}/backup_2025-01-01.json` in your Google Drive
  - Keeps last 20 backups per app automatically
- **Import**: Browse Drive backups → click a file → select keys → restore to localStorage
- **Settings**: View/copy your script URL, inspect localStorage, backup config to Drive

---

## Security

- Username + password are stored only in your Apps Script (your Google account)
- The web app never stores your password permanently (session only)
- All data goes directly from your browser → your Apps Script → your Drive
- No third-party servers involved

---

## Recovering if you forget the Script URL

Open **Google Drive → DriveSync_Backups → _config.json** — it contains your Script URL, username, and save date.